President Biden hosted a state dinner at the White House to celebrate the 70th anniversary of the alliance between the Republic of Korea and the United States. President Yoon and Mrs. Kim of South Korea were in attendance. The visit included a visit to the Korean veterans war memorial, where they paid tribute to fallen soldiers. The alliance between the two countries was born out of a belief in democracy, liberty, and security. President Biden emphasized the importance of working together to make the world better for future generations. He expressed optimism about the future of the alliance. President Yoon thanked the guests for their support of the alliance and quoted an Irish poet to highlight the importance of admired behavior in building relationships. He expressed confidence in the alliance lasting for another seven decades and beyond, contributing to peace and security in the Indo-Pacific and the world. The dinner was seen as a historic moment for the alliance, marking a new chapter in its history.